00:28.240 --> 00:37.760
The first epistle of Paul to the Corinthians, King James Version, Chapter Seven.

00:40.220 --> 00:44.480
Now, concerning the things whereof ye wrote unto me,

00:44.980 --> 00:48.200
it is good for a man not to touch a woman.

00:48.520 --> 00:54.280
Nevertheless, to avoid fornication, let every man have his own wife,

00:54.280 --> 00:58.620
and let every woman have her own husband.

00:59.640 --> 01:04.980
Let the husband render unto the wife due benevolence,

01:05.280 --> 01:08.840
and likewise also the wife unto the husband.

01:09.680 --> 01:13.980
The wife hath not power of her own body, but the husband,

01:14.320 --> 01:20.660
and likewise also the husband hath not power of his own body, but the wife.

01:20.660 --> 01:27.900
Defraud ye not one the other, except it be with consent for a time

01:27.900 --> 01:32.500
that ye may give yourselves to fasting and prayer,

01:33.360 --> 01:41.420
and come together again that Satan tempt you not for your incontancy.

01:41.980 --> 01:46.280
But I speak this by permission and not of commandment,

01:47.060 --> 01:52.680
for I would that all men were even as I myself.

01:53.200 --> 02:00.280
But every man hath his proper gift of God, one after this manner and another after that.

02:00.920 --> 02:04.140
I say therefore to the unmarried and widows,

02:04.580 --> 02:09.800
it is good for them if they abide even as I,

02:10.160 --> 02:13.840
but if they cannot contain, let them marry.

02:13.840 --> 02:21.860
For it is better to marry than to burn, and unto the married I command.

02:22.780 --> 02:29.800
Yet not I, but the Lord, let not the wife depart from her husband.

02:30.660 --> 02:35.780
But, and if she depart, let her remain unmarried,

02:36.020 --> 02:41.960
or be reconciled to her husband, and let not the husband put away his wife.

02:41.960 --> 02:47.040
But to the rest speak I, not the Lord.

02:47.700 --> 02:51.220
If any brother hath a wife that believeth not,

02:51.580 --> 02:56.600
and she be pleased to dwell with him, let him not put her away.

02:57.120 --> 03:01.920
And the woman which hath a husband that believeth not,

03:02.460 --> 03:06.860
and if he be pleased to dwell with her, let her not leave him.

03:07.420 --> 03:12.140
For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife,

03:12.460 --> 03:17.300
and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the husband.

03:17.760 --> 03:22.700
Else were your children unclean, but now are they holy.

03:23.520 --> 03:27.640
But if the unbelieving depart, let him depart.

03:28.260 --> 03:33.320
A brother or a sister is not under bondage in such cases,

03:33.800 --> 03:36.840
but God hath called us to peace.

03:36.860 --> 03:42.200
For what knowest thou, O wife, whether thou shalt save thy husband?

03:42.780 --> 03:47.680
Or how knowest thou, O man, whether thou shalt save thy wife?

03:48.220 --> 03:54.560
But as God hath distributed to every man, as the Lord hath called everyone,

03:55.060 --> 03:59.440
so let him walk, and so ordain I in all churches.

04:00.060 --> 04:03.020
Is any man called being circumcised?

04:03.620 --> 04:06.400
Let him not become uncircumcised.

04:06.860 --> 04:10.060
Is any called in uncircumcision?

04:10.700 --> 04:13.180
Let him not be circumcised.

04:14.140 --> 04:18.420
Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing.

04:18.940 --> 04:22.280
But the keeping of the commandments of God,

04:22.760 --> 04:27.860
let every man abide in the same calling wherein he was called.

04:28.400 --> 04:30.560
Art thou called being a servant?

04:30.860 --> 04:36.440
Care not for it, but if thou mayest be made free, use it rather.

04:36.860 --> 04:42.880
For he that is called in the Lord being a servant is the Lord's free man.

04:43.460 --> 04:50.360
Likewise also, he that is called being free is Christ's servant.

04:51.180 --> 04:53.820
Ye are bought with a price.

04:54.520 --> 04:57.400
Be not ye the servants of men.

04:58.060 --> 05:03.880
Brethren, let every man wherein he is called, therein abide with God.

05:03.880 --> 05:08.660
Now, concerning versions, I have no commandment of the Lord,

05:09.060 --> 05:15.540
yet I give my judgment, as one that hath obtained mercy of the Lord to be faithful.

05:16.060 --> 05:21.420
I suppose, therefore, that this is good for the present distress.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.960
I say that it is good for a man so to be.

05:26.480 --> 05:28.540
Art thou bound unto a wife?

05:28.940 --> 05:30.820
Seek not to be loosed.

05:31.040 --> 05:32.900
Art thou loosed from a wife?

05:32.900 --> 05:35.120
Seek not a wife.

05:36.360 --> 05:40.660
But, and if thou marry, thou hast not sinned.

05:40.820 --> 05:44.820
And if aversion, marry, she hath not sinned.

05:44.880 --> 05:50.140
Nevertheless, such shall have trouble in the flesh, but I spare you.

05:50.660 --> 05:54.280
But, this I say, brethren, the time is short.

05:54.520 --> 06:00.360
It remaineth that both they that have wives be as though they had none,

06:00.360 --> 06:03.820
and they that weep as though they wept not,

06:04.360 --> 06:07.840
and they that rejoice as though they rejoiced not,

06:08.240 --> 06:12.440
and they that buy as though they possessed not,

06:12.580 --> 06:21.200
and they that use this world as not abusing it for the fashion of this world passeth away.

06:21.720 --> 06:26.480
But I would have you without carefulness.

06:26.480 --> 06:32.020
He that is unmarried careth for the things that belong to the Lord,

06:32.620 --> 06:35.100
how he may please the Lord.

06:35.440 --> 06:40.480
But he that is married careth for the things that are of the world,

06:40.780 --> 06:43.220
how he may please his wife.

06:43.840 --> 06:48.900
There is difference also between a wife and a virgin.

06:49.500 --> 06:53.040
The unmarried woman careth for the things of the Lord,

06:53.040 --> 06:57.760
that she may be holy both in body and in spirit.

06:58.440 --> 07:02.480
But she that is married careth for the things of the world,

07:02.900 --> 07:05.480
how she may please her husband.

07:06.160 --> 07:12.940
And this I speak for your own profit, not that I may cast a snare upon you,

07:13.240 --> 07:21.220
but for that which is comely and that ye may attend upon the Lord without distraction.

07:21.940 --> 07:29.900
But if any man think that he behaveeth himself uncumbly toward his virgin,

07:30.380 --> 07:34.480
if she pass the flower of her age and need so require,

07:35.000 --> 07:37.060
let him do what he will.

07:37.300 --> 07:39.960
He sinneth not, let them marry.

07:40.480 --> 07:45.020
Nevertheless, he that standeth steadfast in his heart,

07:45.260 --> 07:49.020
having no necessity but hath power over his own will,

07:49.020 --> 07:55.340
and hath so decreed in his heart that he will keep his virgin doeth well.

07:55.800 --> 07:59.500
So then, he that giveth her in marriage doeth well,

07:59.880 --> 08:03.500
but he that giveth her not in marriage doeth better.

08:04.260 --> 08:08.680
The wife is bound by the law as long as her husband liveth.

08:09.040 --> 08:15.960
But if her husband be dead, she is at liberty to be married to whom she will,

08:16.300 --> 08:17.920
only in the Lord.

08:18.540 --> 08:23.260
But she is happier if she so abide after my judgment,

08:23.660 --> 08:28.660
and I think also that I have the Spirit of God.

08:30.340 --> 08:31.700
Chapter 8

08:32.480 --> 08:38.860
Now, as touching things offered unto idols, we know that we all have knowledge.

08:40.200 --> 08:44.100
Knowledge puffeth up, but charity edifyeth.

08:44.100 --> 08:52.480
And if any man think that he knoweth anything, he knoweth nothing, yet as he ought to know.

08:53.100 --> 08:57.580
But if any man love God, the same is known of him.

08:58.640 --> 09:05.160
As concerning therefore the eating of those things that are offered in sacrifice unto idols,

09:05.600 --> 09:12.020
we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is none other God but one.

09:12.480 --> 09:20.700
For though there be that are called gods, whether in heaven or in earth,

09:21.000 --> 09:24.140
as there be gods many, and lords many.

09:24.560 --> 09:31.800
But to us there is but one God, the Father of whom are all things, and we in him,

09:32.240 --> 09:40.700
and one Lord, Jesus Christ, by whom are all things, and we by him.

09:40.700 --> 09:44.820
Howbeit there is not in every man that knowledge.

09:45.280 --> 09:53.120
For some, with conscious of the idol, unto this hour eat it, as a thing offered unto an idol,

09:53.520 --> 09:56.780
and their conscious being weak is defiled.

09:58.000 --> 10:04.500
But me commendeth us not to God, for neither if we eat are we the better,

10:04.900 --> 10:08.760
neither if we eat not are we the worse.

10:09.320 --> 10:16.380
But take heed, lest by any means this liberty of yours become a stumbling block

10:16.380 --> 10:18.040
to them that are weak.

10:18.620 --> 10:25.440
For if any man see thee which hath knowledge sit at meat in the idol's temple,

10:25.860 --> 10:32.720
shall not the conscious of him which is weak be emboldened to eat those things which are offered

10:32.720 --> 10:33.760
to idols.

10:34.480 --> 10:41.640
And through thy knowledge shall the weak brother perish, for whom Christ died.

10:42.360 --> 10:52.860
But when ye sin so against the brethren, and wound their weak conscious, ye sin against Christ.

10:53.220 --> 11:02.400
Wherefore, if meat make my brother to offend, I will eat no flesh while the world standeth.

11:02.720 --> 11:05.460
Lest I make my brother to offend.

11:06.940 --> 11:09.060
End of chapter 8.

11:10.360 --> 11:13.560
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

